					<description><![CDATA[&#8220;AppInit_DLLs&#8221; is a powerful, yet often overlooked, mechanism in Windows that attackers frequently exploit for persistence, privilege escalation, and code injection. This technique allows adversaries to load their malicious Dynamic Link Libraries (DLLs) into nearly every process that loads user32.dll, which is most user-mode applications. Here&#8217;s a breakdown of how attackers leverage AppInit_DLLs: Understanding AppInit_DLLs [&#8230;]]]></description>
		
